cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their communication protocols.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses collaborative learning among sensor devices.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes distributed data storage algorithms.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is mentioned in the title and could be relevant to the specific application of monitoring and measuring phenomena in pilgrimage.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with designing efficient strategies for data collection and storage in a network of sensor devices.
